\begin{center}
{\bf ABSTRACT}
\end{center}
\begin{quotation}
We study the constraint structure of the topologically massive
theory with one- and two-form fields in the framework of
Batalin-Fradkin-Tyutin embedding procedure. Through this analysis
we obtain a new type of Wess-Jumino action with novel symmetry,
which is originated from the topological coupling term, as well as
the St\"uckelberg action related to the explicit gauge breaking
mass terms from the original theory.

\vskip 0.5cm

\noindent PACS: 11.10.Ef, 11.30.Ly, 11.15.-q\\
\noindent Keywords: Topological mass generation; Hamiltonian and
Lagrangian embedding; Antisymmetric tensor gauge fields\\
\end{quotation}
